mage/15837144 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Upgrades for rings</span><hr size=1> I dont understand why the Shadel Bandit Ring is commonly referred to as an upgrade to the velium fire opal. Sure ist GREAT for hybrids, the extra 110 mana aint bad, plus some resists. All we get of use is resists though, If im on raids i have rings for that already, is losing 10hp worth 5cr and 10 dr? Plus they weigh 0.5 each.  Particularily with the high price of theses these shadel rings and the fact that they are caster items for classes that can use such things, i dont see much reason to warrant the extra cash for them, they are way more expensive than 6/65.  <p><img src=http://newbie.tscentral.net/images/TalkingAbout.jpg><br><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=140534">My Magelo Profile</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucurscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>curscale</A> at: 8/12/02 4:24:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udubbo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dubbo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/12/02 10:59:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10839.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Upgrades for rings</span><hr size=1> &quot;Ring of the Sky is nice if your guild is NTOV capable.&quot;<br><br>Eashen is cake, and your guild doesn't have to be NToV capable to kill 'em - for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> most</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> intents and purposes he may as well be in west wing. ;)<br><br>Ring of the Sky has been on my wish list for quite some time. Unfortunately, out of tons of Eashen kills, he's only dropped 1 lousy steenkin measley freakin ring. We don't farm emp keys currently, but I'll probably wind up with one of those shissar rings if/when we start. Until then, Chardok ring 2 and 6/65 for me... maybe a Reaper's ring, but I doubt I'd burn the points for one.<br><br>I agree with Curscale about the shadel rings for the most part. The only time I break one out of the backpack is when I need the Disease resistance.<br><br>BTW, I'm a rogue, but I think rogues and monks alike can apply the same logic to all of the rings mentioned in this thread, other than possible weight issues (are any of these heavy enough to actually be an issue?).  My 45 monk alt has a Djarn's and a 6/65, but I'd have probably kept the Djarn's on Dubb if I knew it would take this long to upgrade his 6/65. =)  HPs are king.<br><br>I despise Eashen. <p><BR><BR>Marauder <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=50505">Dubb O`Boyce</a><BR>Hobbit Asspoker of <a href="http://www.conceptuelle.com/triune">Triune</a></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showPrevMessage?topicID=10839.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showNextMessage?topicID=10839.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10839.topic&index=11><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.emailToFriend?topicID=10839.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.threadControl?topicID=10839.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/profession